Title: Bio-Digital Forests: AI-Monitored, Environmental-Optimized Urban and Rural Forests
Sections:
	•	Abstract: Sensor-packed, AI-monitored forests capturing carbon, monitoring biodiversity, producing energy.
	•	Problem Statement: Climate change, biodiversity loss, limited real-time environmental data.
	•	Proposed Solution: Combine living forests with embedded modular nodes for compute, monitoring, and prediction.
	•	Technical Design: Sensor integration, edge computing, energy generation, AI modeling.
	•	Deployment & Testing: Pilot forest zones, ecological monitoring, data feedback loops.
	•	Use Cases: Carbon sequestration, biodiversity tracking, environmental research.
	•	Impact & Scalability: Smart forests globally, citizen engagement, climate action.
	•	Future Research & Partnerships: Forestry commissions, climate organizations, universities.
